# PortalJS data scaling — Git LFS wiring (epic po-g9y).
#
# Large dataset files are versioned with Git LFS; their bytes stream to
# Cloudflare R2 through Giftless (see .lfsconfig) and only a small pointer stays
# in git. This keeps data versioned-with-the-repo without git bloat, and lets the
# browser fetch it over HTTP range requests straight from R2 (CORS + ranges are
# configured on the bucket — see giftless/r2-cors.json).
*.csv      filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.tsv      filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.parquet  filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.xlsx     filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text
*.geojson  filter=lfs diff=lfs merge=lfs -text

# Fenced exception (storage decision, po-g9y): the bundled SAMPLE data committed
# under public/data/ (a few KB each) stays INLINE so `create-portaljs` and
# `npm run dev` work offline with zero credentials. Keep these as plain text in
# git; do NOT route them through LFS. This is also the OSS self-host path for
# users running without R2.
public/data/** -filter -diff -merge text
